      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The economic argument should focus on maintaining labor market integrity rather than simply restricting people. Sophisticated framing involves demonstrating how unchecked, undocumented labor can depress wages for low-skilled native workers, creating economic instability for existing citizens. Additionally, proponents should argue that robust border security is fiscally responsible because it prevents the strain on public services—like emergency healthcare and education—that are overwhelmingly utilized by those outside the formal economic and legal structures. This frames enforcement as a necessary function of responsible fiscal governance.",
      "source": "target",
